Figure 3
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="72" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="72">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="72">
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" genus="Dendrostoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Dendrostoma aurorae" order="Diaporthales" pageId="5" pageNumber="72" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="aurorae">Dendrostoma aurorae</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. chinensis" pageId="5" pageNumber="72" rank="species" species="chinensis">D. chinensis</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. shandongense" pageId="5" pageNumber="72" rank="species" species="shandongense">D. shandongense</taxonomicName>
by the existence of obvious central column.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
